# Flat star-shaped disk (z = 0) with irregular, variable-density boundary sampling.
# Fully synthetic (numpy + scipy.spatial.Delaunay, fixed seed); CC0 / public domain.
#
# Regression fixture for MULTI-SOURCE heat-method geodesic distances: seed every
# boundary vertex as a source. The mesh is flat and simply covered, so in the
# near-boundary band the exact geodesic distance to the source set equals the
# euclidean distance to the nearest source (verified against exact polyhedral
# geodesics, agreement ~1e-15). The variable rim sampling makes the heat-method
# Poisson potential spread across the sources, which exposes source-set
# normalization bugs dramatically while correct normalizations stay within a few
# percent of the truth.
